  "text": "diabetic foot ulcers (2,3). Fedorko et al. [CITATION_1] claim that their study population is similar to that of Löndahl et al. (4) . This is not correct, as that study population was older; had a longer diabetes duration, a minimum ulcer duration of 3 months, a longer prespecified minimum prestudy period in a diabetic foot ulcer clinic; and had more comorbidities and higher rates of previous amputation (almost 50 vs. 6%) and previous vascular surgical intervention (55 vs. 12%) at baseline. Further, a mean age of 61 years is notably low (lower than the median age in European diabetic foot ulcer clinics), and there were notably many current smokers (55%).",
